#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:3388
msgid "Life of Uteaqniq Zei"
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:3393
msgid ""
"Uteaqniq Zei knew everything about business. After a miserable childhood in "
"the streets of the imperial capital of Wesnoth, he spent most of his teenage "
"years transforming stolen eggs or smashed glass into warm meals.\n"
"\n"
"During a brief mission in the 2nd legion, he learnt to trade and mastered the"
" art of finding terrific deals. But the gloom of military life was "
"incompatible with his desire of adventure. He therefore resigned to join a "
"small trading company in the west.\n"
"\n"
"Sometime after arriving at Idaamub, Zei met the Dunefolks. He quickly became "
"aware that they had more to offer than exotic weapons and jewels that other "
"companies could not buy. By chance, he had seen the Dunefolks manipulating "
"materials looking like eggshells, thick as a human hand and shining "
"splendidly. Judging by the way they were bending them, Zei estimated they "
"were harder than granite. If he could get enough of them to pave the floor of"
" the house of some fortunate patrician, he would earn quite a sum. \n"
"\n"
"Fortunately for Zei, the shells were worthless to the Dunefolks, who were "
"happy to get rid of them. Their joy doubled when Zei offered them in exchange"
" the same objects many companies had offered them in exchange for their "
"weapons and jewels. \n"
"\n"
"With time, the Dunefolks made Uteaqniq one of their privileged associate, and"
" even went as far as giving him some weapons, despite having refused other "
"interested partners. Uteaqniq’s wealth never stopped growing during those "
"time, and at the time of the punishment of Dunefolks, he had become one of "
"the most fortunate citizens of Idaamub."
msgstr ""

