#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4257
msgid "Biography of Buxo Iova"
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: .\utils\item_list.cfg:4262
msgid ""
"Buxo Iova has the distinction to have been declared dead more often than any "
"other soldier in the history of the 10th Legion. At Yooradweak’s pass, it was"
" said that goblin attackers had defeated him whereas he was beating them to "
"flight three days later. He was then declared dead in a snowstorm while he "
"was gone looking for Caprine, his beloved mule, to finally return, a week "
"later, starving and bothered by a hole in his shoe. \n"
"\n"
"For his allies, stories about his death are entertainment. For his enemies, "
"the object of their desire.  In his opinion, death will only bring him when "
"he will be bored or tired of life and the Reaper better bring reinforcement! \n"
"\n"
"Brought up by a former cook of the 10th Legion, Buxo left to the west of "
"Idaamub as guide for the ofite synod at age 16. He later arrived at Idaamub’s"
" castle and shown a cover letter ordering he was given the position of his "
"mother, but he was found to be worse cook than soldier and he soon found "
"himself at the head of his section, later his company. \n"
"\n"
"Affected to law enforcement at Oa’s gallery during the goblin pretender "
"events, Boxa found himself face to face with goblin attackers that were "
"besieging the Iron Tower of Udxatfe and he beat them alone to flight, sending"
" with only some exceptions all his men to help defend the mines. Few days "
"later, he vanquished two full sections that were trying to pass Udxatfe to "
"reach the Eastern Kingdom and successfully contained the goblin threat to the"
" bay until these lasts finally retreat.\n"
"\n"
"Officially announcing his resignation from the army, he became the guardian "
"of the Western Kingdom, ruling the fortifications and the security of Udxatfe"
" and becoming the owner of the kingdom’s mines. Now retired, he is one of the"
" most respected strategists of the legion and is frequently consulted "
"officious ruler of south of Udxatfe."
msgstr ""

